### Feature Description

I want to be able to use Angular's directive composition API with the sorting behavior made available through the `MatSort` directive. As of this writing, the directive is not standalone, so that is impossible.

### Use Case

Rather than setting the sort properties manually in the template, consumers could make directives which use `hostDirectives` to configure sorting behavior from the template, like this:

```
@Directive({
  selector: '[sortUsingConfig]',
  hostDirectives: [{ 
     directive: MatSort, 
  ],
  standalone: true,
})
export class SortUsingConfigDirective implements OnInit {
  @Input('sortUsingConfig') config: [some config];

  private sortDirective= inject(MatSort);

  ngOnInit() {
    this.sortDirective = {
      ...this.sortDirective,
      start: config.start,
      disableClear: config.disableClear
    };
  }
}

HTML
<table *sortUsingConfig="config">
```
